Terraform
   ↓
AWS VPC (Custom Network)
   ↓
Public Subnets + Internet Gateway
   ↓
EC2 Instances (Amazon Linux 2023)
   ↓
Ansible Dynamic Inventory (AWS)
   ↓
Docker Installation
   ↓
Nginx Container Deployment
   ↓
Application Access via Public IP

☁️ Cloud & Tools Used
Terraform — Infrastructure provisioning
Ansible — Server configuration automation
Docker — Containerization
Amazon Web Services — Cloud provider (EC2, VPC, networking)
Amazon Linux 2023 — EC2 operating system

⚙️ Key Features

🏗 Infrastructure Automation
Custom VPC creation with CIDR-based networking
Public subnets across multiple availability zones
Internet Gateway and route table configuration
Security groups for SSH and HTTP access
EC2 instance provisioning using Terraform



🔄 Configuration Automation
Ansible dynamic inventory using AWS plugin
Automatic EC2 discovery (no static IPs required)
Automated Docker installation and setup
Remote server configuration without manual SSH setup



🐳 Application Deployment
Docker installed via Ansible
Nginx container deployed using Docker CLI
Fully automated container lifecycle management




🚀 Deployment Guide

1. git clone <repo-url>
cd into repo

2. Configure AWS Credentials
aws configure

Ensure your IAM user has permissions for:
EC2
VPC
IAM (if required)

3. Provision Infrastructure (Terraform)
cd terraform
terraform init
terraform apply

This will create:
VPC
Subnets
Route tables
Security groups
EC2 instances

4. Configure Servers & Deploy Application (Ansible)
cd ansible
ansible-playbook playbooks/deploy.yml

Ansible will:
Discover EC2 instances automatically (dynamic inventory)
Install Docker
Configure the system
Deploy Nginx container

5. Access Application

Open in browser:

http://<EC2_PUBLIC_IP>

You should see the Nginx welcome page.



🚀 Future Improvements

This project can be further extended by:

Adding Application Load Balancer (ALB)
Implementing Auto Scaling Groups
Using private subnets + NAT Gateway
Integrating CI/CD pipeline (Jenkins or GitHub Actions)
Storing images in ECR (Elastic Container Registry)
Implementing monitoring (CloudWatch + Prometheus)
